title: Swiss army jet crashes, one person injured
text:
Swiss army jet crashes, one person injured   
Oct 14, 2015 eTN   
A Boeing F/A-18 jets crashed in France while out on a training on Wednesday, in France; said the Swiss army. 
The aircraft was single seated and it took off from a base in Payerne. The accident happened when it came into an uninhabited area not far from a French city calle Besancon. 
The pilot of the aircraft was injured but the cause of the accident is unknown.
